social_posts.post_text: The plan was always to come visit my sister in NYC for Thanksgiving & bring my parents here for the first time. Even without my pops being here with us in the physical world, without a doubt, I felt him right there with us everywhere we went 🕊💛

Fun fact: This star is a Filipino Christmas tradition & they cost a grip. My parents never had one of their own, until back back in the day, my mom & pops was driving and seen one laid up in a neighbors dumpster. They scooped up the mangled star, & my dad fixed it up and redecorated it with lights, garland, and all. I used to tell them I was going to eventually get them a new big shiny one to replace the one they salvaged, but tbh, I wouldn’t trade this one for the world now. This is also probably where I get the “If it’s free, it’s for me” mindset 😂

Despite being the toughest year of my life, that doesn’t take away from every year being better than the last. Did my first art galleries, did my first books, my first passion projects, my first short film, launched my brand, a new company, worked with bucket list clients, did live news interviews, featured on press I dreamed of, and most importantly, served my people. Losses are part of the game of life. Thank you everyone for your continued support on this journey. Cheers to 2022 & an even better 2023 🤲🏽

NYC!!! I am honestly at a loss of words. It was my first time exhibiting my work in this city & I didn’t know what to expect – whether it was a small handful of people showing up or nobody. All I was certain of is it wasn’t going to be THIS. But no, I was proven surprisingly wrong. Every time I looked out at y’all, I was in disbelief seeing y’all enjoy the photos, the stories, the conversations had with each other. The creator community is THRIVING out here, & the love & support for AAPI projects is something we need to keep bringing back, not just during our month, but in normal rotation from here on out, everywhere. Thank you again, each and every one of you, it means so much more than I could ever express🤞🏽🫶🏽
📸: @bloomxmedia @chadbreezy

Here’s a split screen before & after color for the short film I made for the Sony ZV-E1 + just the sound design only. I get asked a lot how I expose for this picture profile. It’s not to a specific number, I just make sure my histogram isn’t clipping in either direction. And that hovers around +1.3 - +2.0 on the exposure meter. Hope that helps! ✌🏽
